Full Title: Professional Communication, Education, and Culture 
Short Title: AFinLA 

Date: 12-Nov-2009 - 13-Nov-2010
Location: Tampere, Finland 
Contact Person: Mikel Garant
Meeting Email: mikel.garant@tamk.fi
Web Site: http://www.tamk.fi/news/en/2655 

Linguistic Field(s): Applied Linguistics 

Call Deadline: 10-Sep-2009 

Meeting Description:

Finnish Association of Applied Linguistics 
Autumn Symposium at TAMK on 12. - 13.11.2009
Friday, February 20, 2009 

Link to this article: http://www.tamk.fi/news/en/2655

The annual Autumn Symposium of the Finnish Association of Applied Linguistics 
(AFinLA) is to be held in at TAMK University of Applied Sciences,Tampere, 
Finland. November 12-13, 2009. 

Main Speakers:
Anna Mauranen, University of Helsinki, Finland
Keith Richards, University of Warwick, England
Balázs Heidrich, Budapest Business School, Hungary 

The theme is 'Professional Communication, Education, and Culture'.

Papers are sought related to the conference theme.  Traditionally, the majority
of the papers are presented in Finnish. However, because of the need to attract
more international participants, it is hoped that there will be a number of
presentations in English. Swedish is Finland's second language so Swedish
language papers are also sought.

Abstract should be 250 words and include the title, author's name and institution. 
The deadline for abstracts is September 10, 2009.
Please send abstracts and inquiries to: sales2009@cs.tamk.fi

Further information:
Mikel Garant: mikel.garant@tamk.fi


 





